In a 9- by 13-inch pan, roast tenderloin in a 400 degrees F oven until thermometer inserted in center of thickest part reaches 135 degrees F for medium-rare, about 50 minutes. Cool beef and thinly slice. Arrange slices, overlapping, on a platter. In a bowl, stir together mustard, honey, and wasabi paste until well blended. Tuck slices of beef into pocket bread halves and add mustard sauce to taste. Serve.